Zelensky: Ukraine was left alone in defending the state
25 February 2022, 02:31
Photo: ©
Vladimir Zelensky. Office of the President of Ukraine
Read ren.tv in
Ukraine was left alone in defending the state. None of the world leaders can guarantee the country's admission to NATO. This was stated by the head of state Vladimir Zelensky during his video message, which was published on the night of February 25.
According to him, among other countries there are no those who are ready to fight together with Ukraine. Zelensky thanked all partner states for their support of the country.
“We remain alone in defending our state. Who is ready to fight with us? Honestly: I don’t see anyone like that... I am grateful to every state that helps Ukraine, but specifically, and not just in words.”
, says the President of Ukraine.
He also stressed that no one gives Ukraine guarantees of joining NATO. According to Zelensky, the leaders of other countries are “afraid.”
Let us recall that on the morning of February 24, Russian President Vladimir Putin, in a televised address to the people, announced the beginning of
military special operation
for the defense of Donbass. Earlier, on February 21, the Russian leader decided to recognize the independence of the Donetsk and Lugansk people's republics.
On February 24, the Russian Ministry of Defense emphasized that there is no threat to civilians in Ukraine, and military strikes are targeted at Ukrainian military infrastructure.
